description: The hits just keep on coming for the Noble family. Half of them are stranded on a hostile alien world and, back on Earth, an escaped mental patient claims he's Doc Noble - and he's headed straight for Noble Manor! All this, plus Zephyr finally goes into labor. As a special bonus, this collection also contains THE PACT #2, which features Zephyr teaming up with Invincible, ShadowHawk and Firebreather.
name: Vol. 5

description:
Meet the Blackthornes. They're the criminal element's answer to the Noble family -- rich, powerful, and deeply dysfunctional. Hidden agendas, secret romances, and dark pasts converge in this sixth collection of the long-running series.

As a special bonus, this collection also contains a five-page story originally printed in the IMAGE HOLIDAY SPECIAL 2005.

Collects NOBLE CAUSES #13-18.
name: Vol. 6

description:
Race Noble has lost his powers, and he's convinced his life is over. But his wife Liz has never had any superpowers, and she tries to convince him that there's more to life than being a superhero. Meanwhile, Rusty Noble learns a horrible secret about his girlfriend, which sends him on a collision course with his hated half-brother, Frost.

Collects NOBLE CAUSES 19-25.
name: Vol. 7

description:
The lives of the Nobles and the Blackthornes continue to intertwine as Zephyr Noble and Slate Blackthorne enter into a secret affair, and the terminally ill Kitty Blackthorne makes an unthinkable request of Celeste.

Collects NOBLE CAUSES #26-31.
name: Vol. 8

description: Jump ahead five years in the lives of the Noble family! Doc Noble has rededicated the Noble family to be the world's preeminent super-heroes, but even as they take a more pro-active approach to fighting crime on a global scale, they still harbor dark secrets and hidden agendas.
name: Vol. 9

description: Long-kept secrets are revealed in the final volume of the Noble Causes saga as Image Comics' most dysfunctional superhero family returns for their last collection of adventures. Collects NOBLE CAUSES #37-40.
name: Vol. 10

volume.name: Movie Comics Featuring Man from Planet X
Tom and Jerry Present the Two Mouseketeers

description:
The greatest Pokémon trainer of all time returns!

Red's back and he's on a mission to catch all of the Pokémon. But he's finding out there are rivals around every corner. There's Misty, Green, and Blue--they're all searching for Pokémon too. And don't forget about the mysterious Team Rocket! Suddenly, Pokémon are more popular than ever before. Everyone, it seems, wants to get their hands on Mew, Poliwhirl, Bulbasaur, and, of course, the irrepressible electric mouse--Pikachu!!
name: Volume 1

description:
The Jackal has plans for Alpha! Can Spider-Man save his protégé before it’s too late?! Plus: Spidey battles Deadpool, Hypno-Hustler and host of spidey-villains!

Also: Introducing the Scarlet Spider! All of the power, none of the responsibility!

Story and art by Dan Slott, Humberto Ramos, Kevin Shinick, Aaron Kuder, Christopher Yost and Ryan Stegman!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #693, Avenging Spider-Man #13 and Scarlet Spider #1!

76 pages!

The Brood are back, and Kitty Pryde is in big trouble! But Wolverine has gone to the biggest casino in the universe – can the X-students survive without him?! By Jason Aaron and Nick Bradshaw!

Cyclops's X-Men team faces the power of the alien android called Unit - but why does it want Hope?

Features material originally printed in Wolverine & The X-Men #4-6 and Uncanny X-Men #9.

Daredevil faces a web of intrigue as Spider-Man and the Black Cat turn up the heat! Also: danger lurks beneath New York, thanks to the Mole Man! By Mark Waid, Kano and Paolo Rivera!

Avengers Academy meets the X-Men! But why is Finesse attacking Magneto, and will she survive the experience?! By Christos Gage and Sean Chen!

Features material originally printed in Daredevil #8-9 and Avengers Academy #22-23.
